<section>
<title>MADplay :: commandline mp3 player</title>
<subtitle>software by Robert Leslie (2000)</subtitle>

<tip>
<para>Get more informations with:
<screen><prompt>[d:b] ~ #</prompt><userinput>man madplay</userinput> <lineannotation><keycap>[Enter]</keycap></lineannotation></screen></para>
</tip>

<para>
       madplay  is a command-line MPEG audio decoder and player based on the MAD
       library (libmad).
</para><para>
       MAD is a high-quality MPEG audio decoder. It  currently  supports  MPEG-1
       and  the  MPEG-2  extension to Lower Sampling Frequencies, as well as the
       so-called MPEG 2.5 format. All three audio layers (Layer I, Layer II, and
       Layer III a.k.a. MP3) are fully implemented.
</para>

